results.expected_cypher:

expansion.expanded:
{
  "INTENT": "Identify IP addresses that have launched attacks against a broad geographic range by finding those that have attacked more than 10 distinct target countries.",
  "KEY_ENTITIES": {
    "NODES": [
      "IP (properties: address, botnet, pulse_ids)",
      "Country (property: name)",
      "ASN (property: number)"
    ],
    "RELATIONSHIPS": [
      "IP-[:ATTACKS]->Country (relationship properties available: technique, protocol, technology, industry, pulse_id, documented_create_date, documented_modified_date)",
      "IP-[:FROM]->Country (optional contextual enrichment: presumed source/origin country for the IP)",
      "IP-[:BELONGS_TO]->ASN (optional contextual enrichment: ASN ownership/association)"
    ],
    "PRIMARY_PATH": "IP-[:ATTACKS]->Country"
  },
  "FILTERS": [
    "Count distinct target Country nodes reached via ATTACKS per IP",
    "Keep only IPs where the number of distinct attacked countries is > 10",
    "Distinctness is based on unique Country nodes (not number of ATTACKS relationships and not relationship-property variations)"
  ],
  "OUTPUT_FORMAT": {
    "TYPE": "tabular list",
    "FIELDS": [
      "ip_address",
      "distinct_attacked_country_count",
      "attacked_countries (optional list of country names for validation/exploration)",
      "asn_number (optional)",
      "source_country (optional, via FROM)",
      "botnet (optional)"
    ],
    "SORTING": "Sort by distinct_attacked_country_count descending, then ip_address ascending"
  },
  "SUGGESTED_APPROACH": "Traverse from each IP to all target Country nodes through ATTACKS relationships, aggregate the set of distinct countries per IP, compute the distinct count, filter to those above the threshold (10), and return the IP with the computed count (optionally also returning the list of country names and related ASN/source-country context).",
  "NEEDS_DECOMPOSITION": false,
  "SINGLE_TASK": "Return each IP address that has ATTACKS relationships to more than 10 distinct Country nodes, along with the distinct attacked-country count (optionally including the country list and ASN/source-country context)."
}
